_:Nab97cf50e1304a339f5ca5706536a5ab <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Angharad joined Nuclear Restoration Services (NRS) in 2006 as a trainee health physicist. She spent eight years in radiation protection, including four years leading the department. Angharad then joined the Trawsfynydd lead team as EHSS&amp;Q manager before becoming waste operations manager.</p>\n\n<p>She later became site director at Trawsfynydd, making history as the first woman in the UK to run a nuclear decommissioning site. In 2024, Angharad was seconded to the NDA as EHS Director but has now returned to NRS as EHSS&amp;Q Director.</p>\n\n<p>Angharad was among the first cohort to train as a mental health first aider and was a founding member of the NRS Women’s Network. She is president of the Wales Nuclear Forum and a role model across the industry, particularly for women in the energy sector.</p>\n" .
